<P>The twentieth day of February Anno Domini 1795. Before me Matthew Clark&s;on, E&s;q. Mayor of the city of Philadelphia in the &s;tate of Penn&s;ylvania, came the above named Robert Morris, John Nichol&s;on, and James Greenleaf, and acknowledged the above written arti|cles of agreement to be their and each of their act and deed, and de&s;ired the &s;ame to be received as &s;uch, and that
<PB N="25" REF="029220_0024_0FDFF21EB8B44BE0">
it may be recorded. In witne&s;s whereof I have hereun|to &s;et my hand and &s;eal
<FIGURE>
<HEAD>The Seal of the City of Philadelphia</HEAD>
</FIGURE></P>
<CLOSER><SIGNED>MATTHEW CLARKSON, MAYOR.</SIGNED></CLOSER>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="certification">
<OPENER><DATELINE>PENNSYLVANIA <HI>&s;&s;.</HI></DATELINE>
THOMAS MIFFLIN Governor of the Commonwealth of Penn&s;ylvania.
<SALUTE>TO ALL to whom the&s;e pre&s;ents &s;hall come GREETING.</SALUTE></OPENER>
<P>KNOW YE that Matthew Clark&s;on E&s;q.
who&s;e name is &s;ub&s;cribed to the forego|ing in&s;trument of writing was at the time of &s;ub&s;cribing the &s;ame and own is Mayor of the city of Philadelphia in the &s;tate of Penn&s;ylvania, duly appointed and com|mi&s;&s;ioned and full faith and credit is and ought to be given him accordingly.</P>
<P><FIGURE>
<HEAD>Great Seal of the State of Penn&s;ylvania.</HEAD>
</FIGURE></P>
